      • getOrCreatePrototype

        public <BEAN extends Bean> BEAN getOrCreatePrototype(Class<BEAN> type)
        Specified by:
        getOrCreatePrototype in interface BeanPrototypeBuilder
        Type Parameters:
        BEAN - the generic type of the Bean.
        Parameters:
        type - the Class reflecting the Bean.
        Returns:
        the prototype instance of the specified Bean. Will be cached and subsequent calls will return the same instance. For polymorphism this method will create the prototype for all super Bean interfaces and connect them so dynamic properties will also be inherited.
        See Also:
        BeanFactory.createPrototype(Class)

      • createPrototype

        public <BEAN extends Bean> BEAN createPrototype(BEAN superPrototypeBean,
                                                String name,
                                                Bean... superBeanPrototypes)
        Description copied from interface: BeanPrototypeBuilder
        Creates a virtual prototype that allows dynamic beans at runtime (without an corresponding sub-interface existing as Java code).
        Specified by:
        createPrototype in interface BeanPrototypeBuilder
        Type Parameters:
        BEAN - the generic type of the Bean.
        Parameters:
        superPrototypeBean - the main prototype of the Bean.
        name - the explicit name of the Bean.
        superBeanPrototypes - the additional prototypes of the Beans (mixins) that will also be inherited from the prototype to create in addition to the given prototype. They have to be prototypes. The prototype to create must not result in cyclic inheritance or inconsistent properties in case of multi-inheritance.
        Returns:
        the prototype instance of the specified Bean.
        See Also:
        BeanFactory.createPrototype(Class)
